<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-11-30T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-11-30T12:00:00-05:00" n="501" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d501">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">417.00/282: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Munro</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-11-30T12:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November 30,
                                        1927—noon</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>210. Your 330, November 12, 11 a.m. Ascertain whether Claims Commission
                            will pass on the claim of Charles Butters for any damages which may have
                            been caused to the San Albino Mine by bandits in Nueva Segovia
                            subsequent to June 30 last.<note n="68" xml:id="d501fn68">See telegram
                                No. 161, June 30, 1927, 2 p.m., from the Minister in Nicaragua, <ref target="#pg_439">p. 439</ref>.</note> Report by telegraph.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>